  "faq": {
    "title": "FAQ",
    "subtitle": "Frequently Asked Questions",
    "q_start": "Where do I start?",
    "a_start": "Start with the <strong>Assessment</strong>. It detects your English level (A1–C2) and your strengths and weaknesses. With that result you can generate a personalized <strong>Study Plan</strong> that fills your Dashboard with daily lessons. Without the Assessment, the Dashboard is empty.",
    "q_workflow": "What is the full workflow?",
    "workflowStep1": "Register and select your native language",
    "workflowStep2": "Take the Assessment → your CEFR level is detected",
    "workflowStep3": "Generate your Study Plan from the Dashboard",
    "workflowStep4": "Complete your daily lessons (START button in the Dashboard)",
    "workflowStep5": "Use Flashcards to train vocabulary in parallel",
    "workflowStep6": "Practice free conversation with the AI Tutor",
    "q_language": "What language will I learn?",
    "a_language": "English only, for now. The native language you choose at registration is used exclusively for flashcard translations and tutor feedback — it does not change the target language.",
    "q_assessment": "What is the Assessment?",
    "a_assessment": "A 20-question AI-generated test covering grammar, vocabulary, reading comprehension, and sentence transformation, with difficulty ranging from A1 to C1. When you finish, you get your CEFR level, a score, and an analysis of your strengths and weaknesses. This result feeds into the Study Plan and generated Flashcards.",
    "q_studyPlan": "What is the Study Plan and how do I generate one?",
    "a_studyPlan": "After the Assessment, go to the Dashboard and click <strong>Generate Study Plan</strong>. A week-by-week plan with daily lessons tailored to your CEFR level and goals will be created automatically. Each lesson includes multiple-choice and free-writing exercises evaluated by AI.",
    "q_flashcards": "What are Flashcards for?",
    "a_flashcards": "A vocabulary training system using the <strong>SM-2</strong> spaced repetition algorithm. Generate cards on any topic (e.g. \"business\", \"phrasal verbs\", \"food\") with a definition, example sentence, and translation into your native language. The system calculates when to show each card again just before you forget it. Completely independent from the Study Plan.",
    "q_tutor": "How does the AI Tutor work?",
    "a_tutor": "A free-form streaming chat. The tutor knows your CEFR level and weak points to tailor its responses. Ask grammar questions, request explanations, practice writing in English, or just have a conversation. Conversations are saved and accessible from the sidebar across sessions.",
    "q_providers": "Which AI providers does FreeLingo support?",
    "a_providers_intro": "Configurable in <code>.env</code> via <code>LLM_PROVIDER</code>:",
    "provider_ollama": "Local, free. Requires Ollama running on the host. Recommended model: gemma3:12b. May be slow without a GPU.",
    "provider_openai": "OpenAI API (GPT-4o, etc.). Fast and reliable. Requires OPENAI_API_KEY.",
    "provider_anthropic": "Anthropic Claude. Requires ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.",
    "provider_deepseek": "DeepSeek API. Requires DEEPSEEK_API_KEY.",
    "q_invite": "Can I invite other people?",
    "a_invite": "Yes. From <adminLink>Admin → Users</adminLink> the admin can create users directly or generate single-use invite links that expire in 48 hours. Public registration is disabled by default (<code>ALLOW_REGISTRATION=false</code>).",
    "q_password": "How do I change my password or native language?",
    "a_password": "Go to <settingsLink>Settings</settingsLink>. You can update your display name, native language, and password from there."
  },
